10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Serpstat is best suited for SMBs, in house SEOs, budget teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Surfer SEO, meanwhile, shines for content writers, SEO specialists, agencies, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2013, Serpstat describes itself as \"Growth hacking SEO tool for keyword research, rank tracking, and site audit.\" Surfer SEO, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI-powered content optimization tool for data-driven on-page SEO.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Surfer SEO** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0). However, this does not mean Serpstat is a poor choice — far from it. Serpstat excels in its own right, particularly for SMBs and in house SEOs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class content optimization scoring, go with Surfer SEO. If good value for comprehensive features matters more to you, Serpstat is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
